                            head: null,
                            content: "Eurydome has a mean radius of about 0.9 miles (1.5 kilometers), assuming an albedo of 0.04. At a mean distance of about 14.3 million miles (23.1 million kilometers) from Jupiter, the satellite takes about 717 Earth days to complete one orbit.",
