                            content: "Like Carpo, S/2018 J4's very high inclination subjects it to the Lidov-Kozai resonance, where there is a periodic exchange between its orbital eccentricity and inclination while its argument of pericenter oscillates about a constant value without apsidally precessing. For example, the Lidov-Kozai resonance causes Carpo's eccentricity and inclination to fluctuate between 0.19 - 0.69 and 44 - 59°, respectively. S/2018 J4's argument of pericenter oscillates about 270° with respect to the ecliptic, which keeps its perijove always above Jupiter and apojove below Jupiter.",
