                            content: "Tethys is the 16th-largest moon in the Solar System, with a radius of 531 km. Its mass is about 6.17 x 1020 kg(0.000103 Earth mass), which is less than 1% of the Moon. The density of Tethys is 0.98 g/cu.cm, indicating that it is composed almost entirely of water-ice. It is also the fifth-largest of Saturn's moons. It is not known whether Tethys is differentiated into a rocky core and ice mantle. However, if it is differentiated, the radius of the core does not exceed 145 km, and its mass is below 6% of the total mass. Due to the action of tidal and rotational forces, Tethys has the shape of triaxial ellipsoid. The dimensions of this ellipsoid are consistent with it having a homogeneous interior. The existence of a subsurface ocean—a layer of liquid salt water in the interior of Tethys—is considered unlikely.",
